itemDescription: British landowner and Whig politician, of Esholt Hall, Yorkshire, and Frimley Park, Surrey (1790–1871)

wikipedia_page.main: William Rookes Crompton-Stansfield  (3 August 1790 – 5 December 1871) of Esholt Hall, Yorkshire, and Frimley Park, Surrey, was a British landowner and Whig politician who was MP for Huddersfield, Yorkshire, from 1837 to 1853.
